ructures\n\n| Key Pattern | Type | Example Value |\n|-------------|------|---------------|\n| `attr:{ns}:{filepath}:{sha}` | Hash | `{\"1-45\": '{\"author\":\"ai\",\"tool\":\"cursor\"}', \"46-50\": '{\"author\":\"human\"}'}` |\n| `deploy:{ns}:{release}` | String | `\"abc123def\"` |\n\n**TTL:** 1 year for attribution keys, 30 days for deployment keys\n\n---\n\n### 2. Files to Create/Modify\n\n#### New Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `devmemory/attribution/redis_storage.py` | Store attribution in Redis |\n| `devmemory/attribution/api.py` | Fast lookup API endpoint |\n| `devmemory/attribution/config.py` | Redis connection config |\n| `devmemory/integrations/sentry-processor/` | NPM package |\n\n#### Modified Files\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `devmemory/commands/sync.py` | Add Redis storage call |\n| `devmemory/core/config.py` | Add Redis config |\n\n---\n\n### 3. Redis Storage Module\n\n```python\n# devmemory/attribution/redis_storage.py\n\nimport redis\nimport json\nfrom typing import Optional\n\nclass AttributionStorage:\n    def __init__(self, redis_url: str):\n        self.redis = redis.from_url(redis_url, decode_responses=True)\n    \n    def store_attribution(\n        self,\n        namespace: str,\n        filepath: str,\n        commit_sha: str,\n        line_ranges: dict\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Store line-level attribution for a file\"\"\"\n        key = f\"attr:{namespace}:{filepath}:{commit_sha}\"\n        \n        # Store each line range as hash field\n        for range_str, attr in line_ranges.items():\n            self.redis.hset(key, range_str, json.dumps(attr))\n        \n        self.redis.expire(key, 365 * 24 * 3600)  # 1 year TTL\n    \n    def store_deployment(\n        self,\n        namespace: str,\n        release: str,\n        commit_sha: str\n    ) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Store release → commit mapping\"\"\"\n        key = f\"deploy:{namespace}:{release}\"\n        self.redis.set(key, commit_sha, ex=30 * 24 * 3600)  # 30 days\n    \n    def get_attribution(\n        self,\n        namespace: str,\n        filepath: str,\n        commit_sha: str,\n        lineno: int\n    ) -> Optional[dict]:\n        \"\"\"Get attribution for a specific line\"\"\"\n        key = f\"attr:{namespace}:{filepath}:{commit_sha}\"\n        \n        # Get all ranges and find the one containing lineno\n        ranges = self.redis.hgetall(key)\n        \n        for range_str, attr_json in ranges.items():\n            start, end = map(int, range_str.split(\"-\"))\n            if start <= lineno <= end:\n                return json.loads(attr_json)\n        \n        return {\"author\": \"human\"}  # Default\n    \n    def get_commit_for_release(\n        self,\n        namespace: str,\n        release: str\n    ) -> Optional[str]:\n        \"\"\"Get commit SHA for a release\"\"\"\n        key = f\"deploy:{namespace}:{release}\"\n        return self.redis.get(key)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. Lookup API Endpoint\n\n```python\n# devmemory/attribution/api.py\n\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException\nfrom pydantic import BaseModel\nfrom typing import Optional\nfrom devmemory.attribution.redis_storage import AttributionStorage\nfrom devmemory.core.config import DevMemoryConfig\n\napp = FastAPI()\nstorage = AttributionStorage(config.ams_endpoint.replace(\"http\", \"redis\"))\n\nclass AttributionRequest(BaseModel):\n    release: str\n    filepath: str\n    lineno: int\n    namespace: str\n\n@app.post(\"/api/v1/attribution/lookup\")\nasync def lookup_attribution(request: AttributionRequest):\n    # 1. Get commit SHA from release\n    commit_sha = storage.get_commit_for_release(\n        request.namespace, \n        request.release\n    )\n    \n    if not commit_sha:\n        raise HTTPException(404, \"Release not found. Did you deploy?\")\n    \n    # 2. Get line attribution\n    attribution = storage.get_attribution(\n        request.namespace,\n        request.filepath,\n        commit_sha,\n  