            "content": "# DevMemory Sentry Processor\n\nEnriches Sentry error events with AI vs Human bug attribution.\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\n# As standalone package\npip install devmemory-sentry-processor\n\n# Or as part of devmemory extras\npip install devmemory[sentry]\n```\n\n## Quick Start\n\n```python\nimport os\nfrom sentry_sdk import init\nfrom devmemory_sentry import create_before_send\n\n# APP_VERSION must be the commit SHA!\ninit(\n    dsn=os.environ[\"SENTRY_DSN\"],\n    release=os.environ[\"APP_VERSION\"],  # Commit SHA\n    environment=os.environ.get(\"ENVIRONMENT\", \"production\"),\n    before_send=create_before_send(\n        ams_url=os.environ[\"DEVMEMORY_AMS_URL\"],\n        repo_id=os.environ[\"DEVMEMORY_REPO_ID\"],\n    )\n)\n```\n\n## Configuration\n\n### Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Required | Description |\n|----------|----------|-------------|\n| `DEVMEMORY_AMS_URL` | No | AMS API URL (default: http://localhost:8000) |\n| `DEVMEMORY_REPO_ID` | Yes | Repository identifier |\n\n### Programmatic Configuration\n\n```python\nbefore_send = create_before_send(\n    ams_url=\"https://ams.internal\",\n    repo_id=\"payments-service\",\n    timeout=2.0,  # Request timeout in seconds\n)\n```\n\n## What It Does\n\nWhen an error occurs in production:\n\n1. **Extracts stack trace** from Sentry event\n2. **Finds first in-app frame** (your code, not dependencies)\n3. **Calls DevMemory API** to get AI attribution for that line\n4. **Enriches the event** with:\n\n### Tags (Searchable in Sentry)\n\n```python\nevent.tags = {\n    \"ai_origin\": \"ai\",        # \"ai\" or \"human\"\n    \"ai_tool\": \"cursor\",      # cursor, copilot, claude, etc.\n    \"ai_confidence\": 0.95,    # 0-1 confidence score\n}\n```\n\n### Context (Visible in Sentry UI)\n\n```python\nevent.contexts[\"ai_attribution\"] = {\n    \"author\": \"ai\",\n    \"tool\": \"cursor\",\n    \"model\": \"claude-3.5-sonnet\",\n    \"confidence\": 0.95,\n    \"commit_sha\": \"abc123def\",\n    \"filepath\": \"src/auth.js\",\n    \"lineno\": 45,\n}\n```\n\n## Requirements\n\n1. **DevMemory sync must run** after each commit to store attribution in Redis\n2. **Release must be commit SHA** - set `APP_VERSION` to `$CI_COMMIT_SHA` in your deployment\n3. **Network access** from production pods to AMS endpoint\n\n## Example: GitLab CI + Sentry\n\n```yaml\n# .gitlab-ci.yml\nbuild:\n  script:\n    - docker build -t $IMAGE:$CI_COMMIT_SHA .\n    - docker push $IMAGE:$CI_COMMIT_SHA\n\ndeploy:\n  script:\n    # Set APP_VERSION to commit SHA for Sentry\n    - echo \"export APP_VERSION=$CI_COMMIT_SHA\" >> deploy.env\n    - argocd app set myapp --parameter env.APP_VERSION=$CI_COMMIT_SHA\n```\n\n## API Response Format\n\nThe processor expects this response from the attribution API:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"author\": \"ai\",\n  \"tool\": \"cursor\",\n  \"model\": \"claude-3.5-sonnet\",\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"commit_sha\": \"abc123def\"\n}\n```\n\nIf no AI attribution found, defaults to `{\"author\": \"human\"}`.\n",
